This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with Sketch-Based Image Retrieval (SBIR) and proposes a new approach for Zero-Shot SBIR. It also involves disentangling image features into structure and appearance features, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as the proposed approach involves a Bi-directional Domain Translation (BDT) framework, which is a type of generative model that can be used for various machine learning tasks. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with a challenging problem of generalizing from seen to unseen categories, which is a common problem in AI. 

The Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with image retrieval, which is a common multimedia task. 

Finally, the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with retrieving images based on sketches, which is a type of information retrieval task.
